For dosimetric quantities shielding by structures in the lander, etc. is not that important because astronauts will always be shielded to some extent. In the lightest possible shielding during an extravehicular activity (EVA) astronauts will at least be shielded by their spacesuits which typically provide a shielding of 0.3g/cm2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
