				\begin{document}$\sim 60\%$\end{document} of all cases) or γ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$\gamma$\end{document}-decay. Most of the conversion electrons have energies between ∼80\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
