				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$Y$\end{document} axis coordinates computed according to the rows marked “Penetrating Particles” in Table 5. This is the definition of the rightmost panel of the Xmas plot marked as “Penetrate J”. One easily recognizes the fully relativistic particles as a nearly straight line from the bottom to the top and the nearly stopping particles which turn to the right, i.e., towards larger values of 4log2(EI/EA)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
