				\begin{document}$4\log _{2}(E_{I}/E_{A})$\end{document}. Particles which veer to the left move upwards through LND, i.e., away from the Moon. They are part of the secondary particle population which is created by the interaction of (mainly) GCRs with the lunar soil. Penetrating electrons lie at the bottom of this panel and are clearly separated from barely penetrating protons, but not from fully relativistic protons which is as expected.

